This project uses dreamd for cross-session memory — what your agent learns here persists.
Call `search_nodes` at task start to recall prior decisions and patterns; call `append_node` when you discover something worth keeping.
At session start, call `GET /api/v1/preferences` over the Unix socket once, passing the `X-Agent-Root` header set to your project's absolute root path, and use the body to calibrate your `pain` and `importance` scores.
